      A terminal configuration record is one which informs the
      network which terminals belong to which stations, and informs
      the station which terminals are associated with each drop.
 
      This menu allows terminal configuration functions to be performed,
      including: adding, modifying, deleting, and listing terminal
      configurations.
 
      Adding A Terminal Configuration Class
      =========================================
      To add a terminal configuration to the Distributed Network,
      enter "1" (for Add Terminal), and press return.  The program will
      then prompt for the terminal number. If the terminal already exists,
      an error message will be displayed, and you will be prompted for
      terminal information.
 
 
 
 
