      Adding a Terminal Configuration (cont'd)
      ============================================
      If the terminal does not exist, the Add a Terminal Record screen
      will be displayed, requiring the terminal configuration to be input.
      The program will display the valid data ranges for each field, and
      if an invalid value is input, an error message will be displayed,
      and you will be required to input the parameter again. NOTE: if
      you enter "E" while adding, the menu will be displayed and the ADD
      will not be performed!
 
      Modifying a Terminal Configuration
      ==================================
      To modify a configuration, enter "2" (for Modify Terminal Configuration),
      and press return.  The program will then prompt for the terminal number.
      If the terminal does not exist, an error message will be displayed,
      and you will be prompted for another terminal.  If the configuration
      exists, the Modify a terminal configuration will be displayed, and
      the current configuration of the terminal will be output.
 
