      Deleting a Terminal Record
      ==========================
      This option will allow a terminal configuration to be deleted.
      Before performing this option, you should ensure that no stations
      will be effected by deleting this configuration from the database.
      To delete a terminal, enter "3" and press return.  Enter the
      terminal number, and if it exists, the Delete a Terminal screen will
      be displayed. If the record does not exist, an error message will
      be displayed, and you must re-enter the number.  Once the Delete
      Screen has been displayed, look at the configuration information to
      ensure that this is the correct terminal.  If you wish to delete
      it, enter "Y" and press return, and a message will be displayed
      informing that the record was deleted.  If you no not wish to
      delete the record, enter "N" and the terminal will not be deleted.
 
 
 
 
